This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with volumetric image analysis using deep learning techniques. The paper also proposes a novel module for improving the performance of 3D Convolutional Neural Networks, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on biomedical image computing, which could also place it under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper's emphasis on improving the network's representational power suggests that it could also be relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
